%N A396329 Decimal expansion of lim_{s->1} Pi^(s/2)/(s*(s-1)*Gamma(s/2)) - 1/(s-1).
%D A396329 I. S. Gradshteyn and I.M. Ryzhik, Tables of Integrals, Series and Products, 7th ed., Academic Press, 2007, p. 658, eq. (6.468).
%H A396329 Junesang Choi and H. M. Srivastava, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/10652461003593294">Integral Representations for the Euler-Mascheroni Constant gamma</a>, Integral Transforms and Special Functions, Vol. 21, No. 9 (2010), pp. 675-690.
%H A396329 Donal F. Connon, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1005.3469">Some trigonometric integrals involving the log gamma and the digamma function</a>, arXiv:1005.3469 [math.CA], 2010, p. 126, eq. (5.9).
%H A396329 William FitzGerald, <a href="https://wrap.warwick.ac.uk/id/eprint/147965/">Exactly solvable interacting particle systems</a>, PhD thesis, University of Warwick, 2019. See p. 151, eq. (3.63).
%H A396329 Will FitzGerald, Roger Tribe, and Oleg Zaboronski, <a href="http://doi.org/10.1214/20-EJP512">Sharp asymptotics for Fredholm Pfaffians related to interacting particle systems and random matrices</a>, Electron. J. Probab., Vol. 25 (2020), paper 116. See p. 8, eq. (2.28).
%H A396329 Niels Nielsen, <a href="https://archive.org/details/handbuchdertheor0000drni/page/204/mode/1up">Handbuch der theorie der gammafunktion</a>, Teubner, Leipzig, 1906, see p. 204, eq. (11).
%F A396329 Equals log(2*sqrt(Pi)) - 1 + gamma/2, where gamma is Euler's constant (A001620).
%F A396329 Equals gamma - Integral_{t>=1} (1 + sqrt(t))*(omega(t)/t) dt, where omega(t) = Sum_{n>=1} exp(-n^2*Pi*t).
%F A396329 Equals -(1 + Integral_{x=0..1} psi(x) * sin(2*Pi*x)^2 dx), where psi the digamma function.
%e A396329 0.554119955935411826792201842175907139420227208787872...
